nuBASIC NEWS -- History of User-Visible Changes
http://www.nubasic.eu/

Author: Antonino Calderone - antonino.calderone@gmail.com
Copyright (c) 2014-2026

Please send bug reports for nuBASIC and nuBASIC IDE to:
<antonino.calderone@gmail.com>

The Win32/64 build created with Visual Studio 2022 requires the
"Visual C++ Redistributable Packages for Visual Studio 2022".

April 2026
* Released nuBASIC 1.61
- Added ByRef / ByVal parameter qualifiers for Sub and Function definitions.
  ByRef passes the caller's variable by reference so mutations inside the
  procedure propagate back; ByVal (the default) passes by value.  Both
  scalars (Integer, Double, String, …) and user-defined Struct variables
  can be passed ByRef.
- Added support for the Call keyword: `Call ProcName(arg1, arg2)` is now
  a fully supported alternative to the bare `ProcName arg1, arg2` syntax.
- Added the Include / #Include directive: `Include "filename.bas"` loads
  and executes another source file at the point of the directive, enabling
  multi-file programs and shared library files.
- Added byref, byval, call, and include to the set of reserved keywords
  so they cannot be used as user-defined variable or procedure names.
- Updated built-in help: `Help ByRef`, `Help ByVal`, `Help Call`, and
  `Help Include` now display documentation for the new language features.
- Added SCREENLOCK, SCREENUNLOCK, and REFRESH instructions for flicker-free
  graphics rendering. SCREENLOCK suspends the automatic per-primitive screen
  refresh so that multiple drawing commands (Line, Rect, FillRect, Ellipse,
  FillEllipse, TextOut, PlotImage, ...) accumulate on an off-screen back buffer.
  SCREENUNLOCK presents the completed frame in a single blit. REFRESH forces an
  immediate blit without altering the lock state (useful before blocking Input$
  calls or game-over dialogs).
- Fixed window repaint flickering on Windows: text and cursor are now composited
  onto the off-screen back buffer before the single BitBlt to the screen,
  eliminating intermediate visible states during WM_PAINT.
- Updated all graphical example programs to use the new screen-lock pattern:
  breakout2.bas, breakout3.bas, pingpong.bas, nutetris.bas, nutetris3d.bas,
  raycast3d.bas, plane.bas, clock.bas, cartoon.bas, minesHunter.bas,
  tictactoe.bas, line.bas, rosetta.bas, calc.bas.
- Updated built-in help (HELP SCREENLOCK, HELP SCREENUNLOCK, HELP REFRESH).
- CLI: after a graphics program ends, the console automatically overlays a
  "Press any key to continue..." prompt on the graphics frame and waits for a
  key before restoring text mode. No explicit keypress code is needed in
  BASIC programs.
- Fixed rosetta.bas, parabola.bas, bitmap.bas: removed manual keypress code
  now handled automatically by the CLI; rosetta.bas timing messages are now
  drawn with TextOut at distinct positions so they no longer overlap.
- IDE: fixed "Evaluate Selection" (F11) freezing after displaying a result or
  error. The timer that dismisses the annotation was incorrectly re-invoking the
  evaluation every three seconds instead of clearing it; errors also caused a
  stale annotation to be shown. Both issues are now resolved.

March 2026
* Released nuBASIC 1.60
- Added a new console for Windows that does not rely on the standard Windows console application
  (it works both attached to and detached from the IDE interface)
- Updated Scintilla to the latest version
- Added UTF-8 support for string literals and PRINT output: characters outside ASCII (Latin Extended,
  Cyrillic, Greek, CJK, etc.) are now correctly preserved through the tokenizer, interpreter, and
  rendered in the GDI console. Fixes silent stripping of non-ASCII bytes in both the CLI file-loading
  path (nu_interpreter.cc) and the IDE editor path (nuBasicEditor.cc rebuild_code).
- Added hello_world_languages.bas example demonstrating multilingual output in 20 languages

Feb 2022
* Released nuBASIC 1.52
- Bug fix: CONST did not work correctly with strings
- PRINT now supports output of escaped Unicode character sequences
- Updated Scintilla to version 4.3.2

Sep 2019
* Released nuBASIC 1.51
- Fixed an expression parser issue: the unary minus operator could trigger a false syntax error
- Added the STOP statement for compatibility with other BASIC interpreters
- IF now supports implicit GOTO after THEN and ELSE
- Fixed mouse position misalignment on Windows with some high-resolution configurations

Jul 13, 2019
* Released nuBASIC 1.50
- Added READ, DATA, and RESTORE statements

Nov 11, 2018
* Released nuBASIC 1.49 / IDE 1.48 for Windows
- Bug fix: incorrect access to elements of a double array with index greater than 0
- Updated SciLexer to version 4.05
- Added the Conv() function and related conv.bas example
- Added the GetVKey() function
- Added a new text version of the Rosetta example
- Extended function syntax to allow returning an array by value
- Arrays of the same type can now be assigned with a single assignment operation
- Additional improvements and minor bug fixes

Jul 3, 2017
* Released nuBASIC 1.48 / nuBASIC GTK+ IDE 1.48 for Linux
- Ported the IDE to Linux/GTK+
- Changed license to MIT
- Added editor zoom in/out commands
- Added SetTopmost API
- Updated stb_image to version 2.15
- Updated Scintilla to version 3.74

Jan 22, 2017
* Released nuBASIC 1.47
- Added floating-point formatting functions StrP and StrP$
- Added hash table support: HSet(), HGet(), HCnt(), HChk(), HDel()
- Added Any type with type deduction
- Added GetAppPath() API
- Added Quit() API
- Improvements and bug fixes

Dec 22, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.46
- Changed icon layout and toolbar command order
- Bug fix: the IDE did not execute old-style programs if the first line was the special comment "!#"
- Bug fix: the IDE did not clear the "Go to procedures" submenu before building new programs
- Improvements and bug fixes

Dec 15, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.45
- Files can now be opened by dragging and dropping them into the nuBASIC IDE window
- Added GetPixel function
- Changed DbgWindow behaviour while running
- Added new sample program "plane.bas" and related bitmaps
- Improvements and bug fixes

Dec 1, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.44
- Added support for executable .bas programs on Linux:
  your program must begin with #!/<bin path>/nubasic
  (you may use the make_bas_exec.sh script to make a .bas file executable)
- The Windows installer now automatically associates .bas files with nuBASIC.
  Clicking one of these files will run it automatically
- Improvements and bug fixes

Nov 30, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.43
- Added Info Message Window to the IDE
- Added context help (F1);
  online help is now mapped to Ctrl+F1
- Improvements and bug fixes

Nov 25, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.42
- Extended explicit type definition to function return types
- Extended function syntax to support returning struct objects
- Improvements and bug fixes

Nov 24, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.41
- Extended CONST statement syntax to support explicit type declaration
- Added new toolbar buttons for topmost / non-topmost debug window selection
- Added new sample program: clock.bas
- Improvements and bug fixes

Nov 21, 2015
* Released nuBASIC 1.40
- Added explicit type declaration (example: Dim aString As String)
- Added structure support:

  Struct AStructType
     element  As String
     element2 As Integer
     element3(4) As Double
  End Struct

  Dim a As AStructType

  a.element = "Hello World"
  a.element2 = 3
  a.element3(0) = 1.5768
  a.element3(1) = 2.5868
  a.element3(2) = 3.14

- Improvements and bug fixes

